{
  "texts": [
    "To address this limitation, embedding-based techniques have been introduced to enhance the explainability of the recommendations (Wang, Chen, et al., 2018; Wang, He, et al., 2018).",
    "Similarly, various other works on explainable social media recommendations also use a collaborative filtering approach (Ji & Shen, 2016), using dynamic neural recommender (Zhang & Hara, 2023) and explaining recommendations using knowledge graphs (Cai et al., 2023; Liu et al., 2023).",
    "Most of the prior scholarly contributions focus on technical aspects of social media recommendation and significantly less on end user perception of social media recommendation.",
    "In this section, we can observe that researchers focused on the interpretability of models, the explainability of reinforcement learning models, and the model-agnostic behavior of social media recommender systems.",
    "Additionally, the core emphasis of these works pertains to the intrinsic design, configuration, and efficacy of many recommender systems."
  ]
}